    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-27T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11130: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-27T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 27, 1930—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 27—1:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>757. Two Nationalist planes, apparently Douglases, recently delivered, flew over
                    and dropped three bombs which fell in southern part of city this morning at 10
                    o’clock. Planes apparently from Tsinanfu; also used machine gun. Please inform
                    War Department as from Military Attaché. Apparently no great damage was done.
                    One bomb did not explode.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
